      "description": "Status indicating whether the specified context was intended or\nunintended",
      "comments": [
        "Expectation is associated with the outcome of a goal or purpose for what\nis expected to happen i.e. an ex-post indication of what was expected to\nhappen in the specified context. Intention and Expectation are closely\nrelated terms. We recommend using Intention when the entity has the\nability to control the implementation and Expectation for when the\nentity does not have control or for what happens after or beyond the\nexercise of control."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "common_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Expectation Status"
      ],
