    {
      "name": "LegalBasis",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/LegalBasis",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "legal-basis-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Legal basis used to justify processing of data or use of technology in\naccordance with a law",
      "comments": [
        "Legal basis (plural: legal bases) are defined by legislations and\nregulations, whose applicability is usually restricted to specific\njurisdictions which can be represented using dpv:hasJurisdiction or\ndpv:hasLaw. Legal basis can be used without such declarations, e.g.\n'Consent', however their interpretation will require association with a\nlaw, e.g. 'EU GDPR'."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "legal_basis_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
