    {
      "name": "Likelihood",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Likelihood",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "risk-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The likelihood or probability or chance of something taking place or\noccurring",
      "comments": [
        "Likelihood can be expressed in a subjective manner, such as 'Unlikely',\nor in a quantitative manner such as \"Twice in a Day\" (frequency per\nperiod). The suggestion is to use quantitative values, or to associate\nthem with subjective terms used so as to enable accurate interpretations\nand interoperability. See the concepts related to Frequency and Duration\nfor possible uses as a combination to express Likelihood."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "risk_notice_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Likelihood"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:Likelihood",
        "dpv:Likelihood"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:Likelihood",
        "dpv_owl:Likelihood"
      ],
      "is_a": "DpvThing",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Likelihood",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "Notice",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Notice",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "notice-classes, organisational-measures-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "A notice is an artefact for providing information, choices, or controls",
      "comments": [
        "Notice refers to the information whereas Notification refers to the\nprovision of that notice. In several cases, they are used\ninterchangeably - for example Privacy Notice as a measure or control\nrefers to both the information as well as the act of making it\navailable. For 'active' contexts where this distinction is important,\ne.g. data breach notifications, see Notification concept."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "risk_notice_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Notice"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:Notice",
        "dpv:Notice"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
