    {
      "name": "SensitivityLevel",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/SensitivityLevel",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "risk-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Sensitivity' reflects the risk of impact if not secured or utilised with\nappropriate measures and controls e.g. for sensitive data",
      "comments": [
        "ISO/IEC TS 38505-3:2021 defines 'data sensitivity' as the potential harm\nof unauthorised disclosure. DPV's use of the concept goes beyond\ndisclosure as it refers to the level of safeguards or controls the data\nrequires as a reflection of its 'sensitive' nature. To indicate\nquantified levels of sensitivity, e.g. \"high sensitivity\", instances of\nseverity can be directly used or specialised"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "risk_notice_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Sensitivity Level"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:SensitivityLevel",
        "dpv:SensitivityLevel"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:SensitivityLevel",
        "dpv_owl:SensitivityLevel"
      ],
      "is_a": "Severity",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/SensitivityLevel",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "Severity",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Severity",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "risk-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The magnitude of being unwanted or having negative effects such as\nharmful impacts",
      "comments": [
        "Severity can be associated with Risk, or its Consequences and Impacts"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "risk_notice_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Severity"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:Severity",
        "dpv:Severity"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:Severity",
        "dpv_owl:Severity"
      ],
      "is_a": "DpvThing",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Severity",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ActiveRight",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ActiveRight",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The right(s) applicable, provided, or expected that need to be\n(actively) exercised",
      "comments": [
        "Active rights require the entity to expressly exercise them. For\nexample, a Data Subject exercising their right to withdraw their\nconsent."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Active Right"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ActiveRight",
        "dpv:ActiveRight"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ActiveRight",
        "dpv_owl:ActiveRight"
      ],
      "is_a": "Right",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ActiveRight",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "DataSubjectRight",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/DataSubjectRight",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The rights applicable or provided to a Data Subject",
      "comments": [
        "Based on use of definitions, the notion of 'Data Subject Right' can be\nequivalent to 'Individual Right' or 'Right of a Person'"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Data Subject Right"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:DataSubjectRight",
        "dpv:DataSubjectRight"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:DataSubjectRight",
        "dpv_owl:DataSubjectRight"
      ],
      "is_a": "Right",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/DataSubjectRight",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "PassiveRight",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/PassiveRight",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The right(s) applicable, provided, or expected that are always\n(passively) applicable",
      "comments": [
        "Passive rights do not require the entity to request or exercise them.\nThey are considered to be always applicable. For example, the Right to\nPrivacy (in EU) does not require an exercise for it to be fulfilled."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Passive Right"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:PassiveRight",
        "dpv:PassiveRight"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:PassiveRight",
        "dpv_owl:PassiveRight"
      ],
      "is_a": "Right",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/PassiveRight",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "Right",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Right",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The right(s) applicable, provided, or expected",
      "comments": [
        "A 'right' is a legal, social, or ethical principle of freedom or\nentitlement which dictate the norms regarding what is allowed or owed.\nRights as a concept encompass a broad area of norms and entities, and\nare not specific to Individuals or Data Protection / Privacy. For\nindividual specific rights, see dpv:DataSubjectRight"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:Right",
        "dpv:Right"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:Right",
        "dpv_owl:Right"
      ],
      "is_a": "DpvThing",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/Right",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "RightExerciseActivity",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightExerciseActivity",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "An activity representing an exercising of an active right",
      "comments": [
        "There may be multiple activities associated with exercising and\nfulfilling rights. See the RightExerciseRecord concept for\nrecord-keeping of such activities in a cohesive manner."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right Exercise Activity"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:RightExerciseActivity",
        "dpv:RightExerciseActivity"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:RightExerciseActivity",
        "dpv_owl:RightExerciseActivity"
      ],
      "is_a": "OrganisationalMeasure",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightExerciseActivity",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "RightExerciseNotice",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightExerciseNotice",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Information associated with exercising of an active right such as where\nand how to exercise the right, information required for it, or updates\non an exercised rights request",
      "comments": [
        "This concept is intended for providing information regarding a right\nexercise. For specific instances of such exercises, see\nRightExerciseActivity and RightExerciseRecord."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right Exercise Notice"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:RightExerciseNotice",
        "dpv:RightExerciseNotice"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:RightExerciseNotice",
        "dpv_owl:RightExerciseNotice"
      ],
      "is_a": "RightNotice",
      "mixins": [
        "OrganisationalMeasure"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightExerciseNotice",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "RightExerciseRecord",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightExerciseRecord",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Record of a Right being exercised",
      "comments": [
        "This concept represents a record of one or more right exercise\nactivities, such as those associated with a single data subject or\nservice or entity"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right Exercise Record"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:RightExerciseRecord",
        "dpv:RightExerciseRecord"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:RightExerciseRecord",
        "dpv_owl:RightExerciseRecord"
      ],
      "is_a": "RecordsOfActivities",
      "mixins": [
        "OrganisationalMeasure"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightExerciseRecord",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "RightFulfilmentNotice",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightFulfilmentNotice",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Notice provided regarding fulfilment of a right",
      "comments": [
        "This notice is associated with situations where information is provided\nwith the intention of progressing the fulfilment of a right. For\nexample, a notice asking for more information regarding the scope of the\nright, or providing information on where to access the data provided\nunder a right."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right Fulfilment Notice"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:RightFulfilmentNotice",
        "dpv:RightFulfilmentNotice"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:RightFulfilmentNotice",
        "dpv_owl:RightFulfilmentNotice"
      ],
      "is_a": "RightExerciseNotice",
      "mixins": [
        "OrganisationalMeasure"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightFulfilmentNotice",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "RightNonFulfilmentNotice",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightNonFulfilmentNotice",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Notice provided regarding non-fulfilment of a right",
      "comments": [
        "This notice is associated with situations where information is provided\nwith the intention of communicating non-fulfilment of a right. For\nexample, to provide justifications on why a right could not be fulfilled\nor providing information about another entity who should be approached\nfor exercising this right."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right Non-Fulfilment Notice"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:RightNonFulfilmentNotice",
        "dpv:RightNonFulfilmentNotice"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:RightNonFulfilmentNotice",
        "dpv_owl:RightNonFulfilmentNotice"
      ],
      "is_a": "RightExerciseNotice",
      "mixins": [
        "OrganisationalMeasure"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightNonFulfilmentNotice",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "RightNotice",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightNotice",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "rights-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Information associated with rights, such as which rights exist, when and\nwhere they are applicable, and other relevant information",
      "comments": [
        "This concept also covers information about rights exercise, with\ndpv:RightExerciseNotice specifically representing information provided\nin connection with exercising of rights. Both notices may be needed,\ne.g. RightNotice for providing information about existence and exercise\nof rights, and RightExerciseNotice for providing additional information\nspecifically about exercise of rights - such as to request more\ninformation or provide updates on an exercised rights request"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "rights_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Right Notice"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:RightNotice",
        "dpv:RightNotice"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:RightNotice",
        "dpv_owl:RightNotice"
      ],
      "is_a": "Notice",
      "mixins": [
        "OrganisationalMeasure"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/RightNotice",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ConsentControl",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentControl",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-controls-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The control or activity associated with obtaining, providing,\nwithdrawing, or reaffirming consent",
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Consent Control"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ConsentControl",
        "dpv:ConsentControl"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ConsentControl",
        "dpv_owl:ConsentControl"
      ],
      "is_a": "EntityInvolvement",
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentControl",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ConsentExpired",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentExpired",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-status-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The state where the temporal or contextual validity of consent has\n'expired'",
      "comments": [
        "An example of this state is when the obtained consent has been assigned\na duration - which has lapsed or 'expired', making it invalid to be used\nfurther for processing data"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Consent Expired"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ConsentExpired",
        "dpv:ConsentExpired"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ConsentExpired",
        "dpv_owl:ConsentExpired"
      ],
      "is_a": "ConsentStatusInvalidForProcessing",
      "mixins": [
        "ConsentStatus"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentExpired",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ConsentGiven",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentGiven",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-status-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The state where consent has been given",
      "comments": [
        "An example of this state is when the individual clicks on a button,\nticks a checkbox, verbally agrees - or any other form that communicates\ntheir decision agreeing to the processing of data"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Consent Given"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ConsentGiven",
        "dpv:ConsentGiven"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ConsentGiven",
        "dpv_owl:ConsentGiven"
      ],
      "is_a": "ConsentStatusValidForProcessing",
      "mixins": [
        "ConsentStatus"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentGiven",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ConsentInvalidated",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentInvalidated",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-status-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The state where consent has been deemed to be invalid",
      "comments": [
        "An example of this state is where an investigating authority or a court\nfinds the collected consent did not meet requirements, and 'invalidates'\nboth prior and future uses of it to carry out processing"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Consent Invalidated"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ConsentInvalidated",
        "dpv:ConsentInvalidated"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ConsentInvalidated",
        "dpv_owl:ConsentInvalidated"
      ],
      "is_a": "ConsentStatusInvalidForProcessing",
