      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ConsentUnknown",
        "dpv_owl:ConsentUnknown"
      ],
      "is_a": "ConsentStatusInvalidForProcessing",
      "mixins": [
        "ConsentStatus"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentUnknown",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ConsentWithdrawn",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentWithdrawn",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-status-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "The state where the consent is withdrawn or revoked specifically by the\ndata subject and which prevents it from being further used as a valid\nstate",
      "comments": [
        "This state can be considered a form of 'revocation' of consent, where\nthe revocation can only be performed by the data subject. Therefore we\nsuggest using ConsentRevoked when it is a non-data-subject entity, and\nConsentWithdrawn when it is the data subject"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Consent Withdrawn"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ConsentWithdrawn",
        "dpv:ConsentWithdrawn"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ConsentWithdrawn",
        "dpv_owl:ConsentWithdrawn"
      ],
      "is_a": "ConsentStatusInvalidForProcessing",
      "mixins": [
        "ConsentStatus"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ConsentWithdrawn",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ExplicitlyExpressedConsent",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ExplicitlyExpressedConsent",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-types-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Consent that is expressed through an explicit action solely conveying a\nconsenting decision",
      "comments": [
        "Explicitly expressed consent is a more specific form of Expressed\nconsent where the action taken must 'explicitly' relate to only the\nconsent decision. Expressed consent where the consenting is part of\nother matters therefore cannot satisfy the requirements of explicitly\nexpressed consent. An example of explicit action expressing the\nconsenting decision is a button on a web form where the form only\nrelates to consent, or it is accompanied with suitable text that\nreiterates what the consenting decision is about"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Explicitly Expressed Consent"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ExplicitlyExpressedConsent",
        "dpv:ExplicitlyExpressedConsent"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ExplicitlyExpressedConsent",
        "dpv_owl:ExplicitlyExpressedConsent"
      ],
      "is_a": "ExpressedConsent",
      "mixins": [
        "LegalBasis"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ExplicitlyExpressedConsent",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ExpressedConsent",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ExpressedConsent",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-types-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Consent that is expressed through an action intended to convey a\nconsenting decision",
      "comments": [
        "Expressed consent requires the individual take a specific and\nunambiguous action that directly indicates their consent. This action\nmay be a part of other processes such as setting preferences, or\nagreeing to a contract, or other matters not relating to consent. An\nexample of expressed consent is interacting with a checkbox within a\ndashboard or clicking a button on a web form"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Expressed Consent"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ExpressedConsent",
        "dpv:ExpressedConsent"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ExpressedConsent",
        "dpv_owl:ExpressedConsent"
      ],
      "is_a": "InformedConsent",
      "mixins": [
        "LegalBasis"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ExpressedConsent",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ImpliedConsent",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ImpliedConsent",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-types-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Consent that is implied indirectly through an action not associated\nsolely with conveying a consenting decision",
      "comments": [
        "Implied consent is expected to also be Informed Consent. An example is a\nCCTV notice outside a monitored area that informs the individuals that\nby walking in they would be consenting to the use of camera for\nsurveillance."
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Implied Consent"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ImpliedConsent",
        "dpv:ImpliedConsent"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ImpliedConsent",
        "dpv_owl:ImpliedConsent"
      ],
      "is_a": "InformedConsent",
      "mixins": [
        "LegalBasis"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ImpliedConsent",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "InformedConsent",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/InformedConsent",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-types-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Consent that is informed i.e. with the requirement to provide sufficient\ninformation to make a consenting decision",
      "comments": [
        "The specifics for what information should be provided or made available\nwill depend on the context, use-case, or relevant legal requirements"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Informed Consent"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:InformedConsent",
        "dpv:InformedConsent"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:InformedConsent",
        "dpv_owl:InformedConsent",
        "iso29100:Consent"
      ],
      "close_mappings": [
        "iso29100:ConsentMechanism"
      ],
      "is_a": "Consent",
      "mixins": [
        "LegalBasis"
      ],
      "slots": [
        "id"
      ],
      "slot_usage": {},
      "class_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/InformedConsent",
      "@type": "ClassDefinition"
    },
    {
      "name": "ManageConsent",
      "definition_uri": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv/ManageConsent",
      "annotations": [
        {
          "tag": "skos_in_scheme",
          "value": "consent-controls-classes",
          "@type": "Annotation"
        }
      ],
      "description": "Control for managing a given consent in terms of providing, reaffirming,\nor withdrawing it",
      "comments": [
        "Indicates how the data subject can manage their consent in terms of\nproviding it, or reaffirming or withdrawing a given consent. This\nconcept is useful to represent a single location or interface where\nmultiple controls are provided for consent"
      ],
      "in_subset": [
        "consent_subset"
      ],
      "from_schema": "https://w3id.org/lmodel/dpv",
      "aliases": [
        "Manage Consent"
      ],
      "mappings": [
        "dpv:ManageConsent",
        "dpv:ManageConsent"
      ],
      "exact_mappings": [
        "dpv_upstream:ManageConsent",
        "dpv_owl:ManageConsent"
      ],
      "is_a": "ProvideConsent",
      "mixins": [
        "ReaffirmConsent",
        "WithdrawConsent"
      ],
      "slots": [
